This article provides background information on a naturalization ceremony for active duty service members that took place at the White House. President Obama delivered remarks at the ceremony, which recognized the contributions of immigrant members of the U.S. armed forces who chose to become citizens. The article includes a list of the service members who became American citizens during the ceremony. Additionally, it highlights the story of Peter Lemon, a Canadian-born soldier who received the Outstanding American by Choice award for his bravery during the Vietnam War. Lemon survived a mortar attack and fought off enemy soldiers in hand-to-hand combat. He later returned home as a hero and now works as a professional speaker, author, and documentary producer.